This eBook is a copy of William Shakespeare's Romeo and Juliet, originally produced by Project Gutenberg. There is an improved edition available on their website. The eBook is free to use and distribute under the Project Gutenberg License. The eBook includes the full text of the play, including a list of characters and the prologue. The first scene features two servants of the Capulet family, Sampson and Gregory, engaging in a verbal confrontation with two servants of the Montague family, Abram and Balthasar, which quickly turns physical. Benvolio attempts to break up the fight, but Tybalt, a member of the Capulet family, arrives and draws his sword.